From: nix-wasm <eric@codebutler.com>
Subject: [PATCH] wasm: deliver a queued SA_RESTART signal handler before restart (#75)

A blocking syscall interrupted by a signal whose handler was installed with
SA_RESTART (e.g. via signal(), which musl maps to SA_RESTART) returns
-ERESTARTSYS. handle_signal() then keeps -ERESTARTSYS (so the syscall will
restart) and setup_rt_frame() queues the handler by setting _TIF_DELIVER_SIGNAL.

But the queued handler is only ever run by _user_mode_tail in the syscall asm
FOOT, which executes AFTER __wasm_syscall_N returns. The C restart do/while in
WASM_SYSCALL_N re-enters the syscall in-place on -ERESTARTSYS and never returns
to the FOOT, so the handler is never delivered and the restarted syscall blocks
forever. With sa_flags=0, handle_signal() rewrites -ERESTARTSYS to -EINTR
(restart=false) and the loop exits, so the FOOT delivers the handler -- which is
why every signal test (all sigaction sa_flags=0) passes and only SA_RESTART
users hang. Headline symptom: busybox FANCY `ping` sends one ICMP echo then
hangs (its interval SIGALRM handler sendping4, armed via signal(), never runs,
so packet #2 is never sent; `ping -c1` works). See issue #75.

Fix: when the loop is about to restart AND a handler is queued
(_TIF_DELIVER_SIGNAL), run it now via _user_mode_tail() -- the same trampoline
the FOOT uses (it runs the user handler and its sigreturn through the host) --
before restarting. The handler's sigreturn restores pt_regs and unblocks the
signal, so the subsequent restart re-runs the syscall with the original args and
the next signal can interrupt it again (pacing resumes). No host/engine ABI
change: this only reorders existing in-kernel delivery, so ENGINE_ABI is
unchanged.

--- a/arch/wasm/kernel/traps.c	2026-06-26 12:26:05.633753806 +0000
+++ b/arch/wasm/kernel/traps.c	2026-06-26 12:26:05.648383999 +0000
@@ -8,6 +8,14 @@
 #include <asm/ptrace.h>
 #include <asm/syscall.h>
 
+/*
+ * entry.S trampoline that runs any pending signal handler (and its
+ * sigreturn) in userland via the host. Normally reached from the syscall
+ * asm FOOT after __wasm_syscall_N returns; issue #75 also calls it in-loop
+ * to deliver a queued SA_RESTART handler before restarting the syscall.
+ */
+void _user_mode_tail(void);
+
 static inline void _exception_enter(struct pt_regs *regs)
 {
 	regs->cpuflags = cpuflags_load();
@@ -64,6 +72,13 @@
 				default:					\
 					restart = false;			\
 				}						\
+				/* #75: a SA_RESTART (or NOINTR) restart left a signal	\
+				 * handler queued by setup_rt_frame(); it must RUN before	\
+				 * we restart, else (e.g. busybox ping's sendping4) it is	\
+				 * never delivered and the restarted syscall hangs. */	\
+				if (restart && (current_thread_info()->flags &		\
+					_TIF_DELIVER_SIGNAL))			\
+					_user_mode_tail();			\
 			} while (restart);					\
 		} else {							\
 			irqentry_state_t state = irqentry_nmi_enter(regs);	\
